<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF110-343-418  </DOCNO><DOCID>10 343 418.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE: Work-Group Computing Report  July 2 1990 v1 n6 p28(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Biometric ID: California to issue $40 million Identix contractvalued at $40 million. Fingerprint acquisition andamp; use is growingindustry. (California department of justice awards CAL-ID LiveScan contract)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Identix Inc. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    IDXX.andO;Topic:     California. Department of JusticeGovernment ContractsBiometricsData SecurityAccess ControlsScanning Devices.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Identix Inc., a manufacturer of biometric fingerprint acquisition equipment,has received a letter from the California Department of Justice stating thedepartment's intention to award the CAL-ID Live-Scan contract to Identix.andM;The notification follows the successful completion by Identix of the state'squalifying benchmark tests.andM;The contract, which will be the largest Live-Scan fingerprinting equipmentcontract award to date, calls for Identix to provide up to 600 TouchPrintfingerprint scanning systems to California state, county and city lawenforcement authorities.andP;  The state will pay the majority of costs for citiesand counties that install the machines.andM;Once installed, the TouchPrint system will allow law enforcement authoritiesto electronically scan and print fingerprints at the point-of-booking.andO;Simultaneously, the fingerprints can be transmitted over telephone lines to acomputer system for identification matching in a fraction of the time itcurrently takes through manual processing.andM;Just the week befor, Identix was awarded a $3 million Group Bull contract.andM;Identix, located in Sunnyvale, designs, manufactures and markets a family ofidentity verification systems that combine high accuracy with userfriendliness.andM;Key Executives: Randy Fowler, President, IdentIX.andO;</TEXT></DOC>